    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Centrifugal blood pump hemolysis applicability domain",
      "description": "Applicable to continuous-flow centrifugal blood pumps operating in the ventricular assist device configuration for adult patients. Scope is limited to Newtonian blood analogue rheology at hematocrit 40±5%, pump speeds between 2400 and 3600 RPM, and flow rates between 3 and 7 L/min. Excludes pulsatile-flow LVAD configurations, paediatric pump geometries, and non-Newtonian shear-thinning regimes where the power-law viscosity exponent deviates by more than 10% from the Newtonian baseline."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "VAD operating envelope: flow rate, speed, and pressure head bounds",
      "description": "Flow rate: 3.0–7.0 L/min (nominal 5 L/min); pump rotational speed: 2400–3600 RPM in 300 RPM increments; inlet pressure: 5–15 mmHg; outlet pressure head: 60–120 mmHg; fluid temperature: 37±1 °C; hematocrit: 35–45%; Reynolds number range 4 000–18 000 based on impeller tip diameter. Five operating points (3 L/min × 2400 RPM, 4 L/min × 2700 RPM, 5 L/min × 3000 RPM, 6 L/min × 3300 RPM, 7 L/min × 3600 RPM) constitute the full validation matrix. Extrapolation beyond these bounds is not supported by the current evidence package."
    }
  },
