      "rationale": "The primary validation QoI is the normalised index of hemolysis (NIH, g/100L) computed from the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model with coefficients α=0.785, β=0.062, C=3.62×10⁻⁷, identical to the COU simulation configuration. No surrogate QoI substitution is made. The NIH maps directly to the clinical threshold of < 0.1 g/100L specified in the device design requirement. Achieved level 4 meets requirement."
