        "description": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated with residuals dropping at least 4 orders of magnitude. Round-off error must be assessed by running a double-precision reference case. Solver settings (relaxation factors, convergence criteria) must be documented and justified."
      },
      "rationale": "All simulations run in double precision. Continuity, momentum, and scalar residuals converged to < 10⁻⁶ (6 orders of magnitude). Round-off error estimated at < 10⁻¹² relative to NIH magnitude — negligible. Under-relaxation factors (velocity 0.7, pressure 0.3, scalar 0.5) are documented and consistent with solver best-practice guidelines for rotating machinery. Achieved level 4 exceeds the required level 3."
