        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criterion — MRL 5",
        "description": "Turbulence model selection must be justified by comparison of at least two turbulence models against experimental velocity data. The hemolysis constitutive model (power-law) must be justified by comparison to published red blood cell damage data. Model-form uncertainty must be quantified and included in the total uncertainty budget."
      },
      "rationale": "SST k-ω and realizable k-ε turbulence models were compared against PIV velocity data; SST k-ω yielded lower FBVI error (0.09 vs. 0.14) and was selected. Model-form uncertainty estimated by the difference in NIH predictions between the two models (ΔNIH = 0.0031 g/100L) and propagated into the total uncertainty budget. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was selected based on its validation against Wurzinger et al. (1986) RBC damage data at shear stresses 50–400 Pa. Achieved level 4 meets requirement."
