        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criterion — MRL 5",
        "description": "All model input parameters must be characterised with uncertainty distributions. Sensitivity analysis must identify the top contributors to output uncertainty. Inputs with coefficient of variation > 5% must be treated as uncertain in the Monte Carlo ensemble."
      },
      "rationale": "Seventeen model input parameters were characterised with probability distributions (normal, log-normal, or uniform as appropriate) based on measurement data or literature. Monte Carlo ensemble of 2 000 runs propagated input uncertainty through the hemolysis model. Sensitivity analysis (Sobol indices) identified fluid viscosity (S_T = 0.31), hemolysis model coefficient C (S_T = 0.27), and rotational speed (S_T = 0.19) as dominant contributors. All inputs with CV > 5% (viscosity, C, α) were included as uncertain. Achieved level 4 meets requirement."
